data.name: textNextPage.ToolTip
data.value:
Key to the next page.
Eg "resultats/1/#Search#/#Page#.html".
At the end of each page, the grabber fetches the source code in a string results resultats/1/#Search#/pagecourante+1.html
If found, it will ask the user to move to the next page.

data.name: comboBox1.ToolTip
data.value:
Parameter list.
With the exception of "Start / End Result List," all parameters reported for 1 and 1 single result list.
Start / End Result List: Not mandatory, but strongly recommended! it reduces the source code to have that part of the results. Start / End Title: Required. Start / End Year: Not required. Start / End Director: Not required. Start / End Detail Page URL: Required.

data.name: TextURL.ToolTip
data.value:
URL of the search page.
On that site, search with a keyword relevant (eg "black"), to get many results. Some sites offer first a little list of results sorted by categories with a link "more results" for example. That's what you need to copy link: results will be more and especially the page will be easier to cut. (1 class only).
Important: You must replace the search string that you used with the string # # Search in the url and the page number from page # # (if present).

data.name: cbParamDetail.ToolTip
data.value:
Liste des paramtres.
Start / End Detail Page : Permet de rduire le code source la section qui nous intresse. Start / End Original Title : Titre original. Start / End Translated Title : Titre traduit. Start / End URL cover : URL de l'affiche. Start / End Rate 1 : Note 1. Start / End Rate 2 : Note 2. Start / End Synopsys : Descriptif du film. Start / End Director: Director (s) Start / End Producer: Producer (s) Start / End Actors: Actors Start / End Country: Country Start / End Genre: Genre film. Start / End Year: Year. Start / End URL Redirection cover: For posters better, it is sometimes need to click on another tab. This setting allows you to find in the code address tab. Then use Start / End cover to find the URL address of the poster in this new page.

data.name: textURLPrefix.ToolTip
data.value: Enter here the prefix that will be used for relative URLs. For example, some sites, the URL of the poster starts with "/ shows / movies ...". This parameter makes it possible to define the beginning of the URL ("http://lesite.com).
